Purdue Extension Randolph County
May 15 at 5:18 PM Â·

Purdue Extension events may resume July 1 in compliance with the Back on Track Indiana plan. This means 4-H fairs and 4-H events at county fairs could be held in July. Please keep in mind: fairs and events will look different this summer. Restrictions and safety precautions will be required, and these will vary by community. Please give your county extension staff the time and space they need to communicate full details with 4-H families and volunteers.

As of today we do not have a formal announcement regarding the Randolph County 4-H events and future dates. Please note we are still planning to have our 4-H events, itâ€™s just going to look different this year.

WHY you might ask

Simply because we still need to meet with local officials and Randolph County 4-H Inc Executive Board Members. Randolph County 4-H Inc. will be meeting next week to discuss what fair will look like and how we proceed. 4-H Inc. will also need to take into account guidance from local authorities before making any announcements.

post_text: Chrome book drop off will be on May 21st & May 22. May 21st will be from 8:00 am to 3:00 pm. May 22nd will be from 12:00 noon until 7:00 pm. Please bring your chrome book to door #25 on the north side of the building. Someone will come and get your chrome book. We will also return any student supplies that have been left at school. Please make sure that the charger is in the chrome book case. You may also return any other items that belong to the school such as textbooks, library books, etc. If you have any assignments that need to be turned in, you may do that also. If you have any questions please contact Annette Wilson at 765-576-0969.

Randolph County Promise
February 21, 2019 at 1:46 PM Â·

ATTENTION Monroe Central, Union, Randolph Southern, and North Side third graders and their parents!!! This Saturday is the RC Promise FREE MOVIE MATINEE just for YOU! Get your FREE tickets from your school office and meet us at Towne Square Cinema in Winchester Saturday, February 23. (Doors open at 12:00 with the movie beginning at 1:00) You will receive free popcorn and drink as well as seeing The Lego Movie 2. This is your chance for your parents to sign you up for your FREE Randolph County Promise CollegeChoice 529 plan. The deadline is quickly approaching. All third graders who sign up will have $25 deposited in their account AND be eligible to participate in Champion Week to earn an additional $75 deposit! We are looking forward to seeing you there!!
If you are unable to attend, you can sign up at www.promiseindiana.org.
